<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-494] NIO HTTP transport: GET request without operation name causes Synapse to hang</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-494</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Start Synapse with sample 150.&lt;br/&gt;
2) Issue the following request in a browser: &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8280/services/StockQuoteProxy&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8280/services/StockQuoteProxy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Result: Synapse hangs and the request eventually times out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that this issue is independent of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-479&quot; title=&quot;Failure in REST test case&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SYNAPSE-479&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SYNAPSE-479&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, i.e. it has been observed both before and after the change.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
